  "detailed_description": [
    {
      "heading": "Comprehensive IoT Gateway",
      "text": "The MikroTik KNOT LR8G Kit is an advanced industrial IoT gateway designed to unify multiple communication technologies in one compact device. It supports LoRa® for long-range, low-power sensor networks, LTE CAT-M1 and NB-IoT for cellular data, 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi for local connectivity, and Bluetooth 5.2 for energy-efficient sensor integration. GPS functionality ensures accurate positioning and time synchronization, making the device suitable for mobile and remote deployments. This flexibility allows businesses to connect and manage thousands of devices, from smart meters and environmental sensors to tracking and logistics equipment. The integrated LoRa® interface works on the 868 MHz band, ensuring stable long-distance communication in interference-prone environments."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Industrial-Grade Performance",
      "text": "The MikroTik KNOT LR8G Kit is engineered for demanding professional environments. Powered by a 650 MHz CPU, 64 MB of RAM, and 128 MB NAND storage, it runs RouterOS v7 with License Level 4, delivering advanced routing, security, and management features. The device supports Modbus, RS485, and GPIO for integration with industrial controllers, sensors, and legacy systems. It also features a microUSB OTG port for additional peripherals. The hardware design ensures energy efficiency, with power consumption around 6 W, while providing stable performance 24/7. Its rugged construction enables reliable operation in harsh environments, with a wide temperature range from −40 °C to +70 °C and humidity tolerance up to 95% non-condensing. The device includes mounting brackets for wall or DIN-rail installation, ensuring easy integration into control cabinets, vehicles, or industrial enclosures.\n\nThe KNOT LR8G Kit combines compact design with professional durability. Its housing is designed for industrial applications, offering long-term reliability in smart infrastructure and mission-critical systems. The device supports multiple power input options, including PoE, DC jack, or microUSB, giving flexibility for deployment in diverse power environments. Antenna connectors for each wireless interface allow for optimized performance in long-distance or high-density applications. Security and stability are reinforced through RouterOS features such as VPN, firewall, VLAN, and traffic management, ensuring safe integration into enterprise networks. The gateway enables seamless expansion of IoT systems without heavy infrastructure costs, thanks to its ability to bridge LoRa® sensors with IP or cellular networks."
    }
  ],
